lowing enhanced cleaning and disinfecting protocols that includes cleaning commonly used areas and wiping down equipment and high touch surfaces more frequently.--sep-- --sep-- --sep--Protective Barriers--sep--We\u2019re installing protective barriers at all check lanes, Pharmacy Counters, Starbucks and The Little Clinic locations, to help protect both customers and associates.--sep-- --sep--Personal Protective Equipment--sep--There is a national shortage of personal protective equipment like this, and we fully support America\u2019s health care workers having first priority to obtain the equipment they need. We are advocating to government officials at all levels for help securing a priority place in line for all grocery workers - after health care workers - to have access to protective masks.--sep--Emergency Leave Guidelines--sep--We have enacted Emergency Leave Guidelines, allowing paid time off for associates diagnosed with COVID-19, placed under mandatory quarantine and paid time off for self isolation and symptoms as verified by an accredited health care professional. All eligible associates will receive their standard pay for up to two weeks (14 days).--sep--For those affected by COVID-19, the organization has also made available $5 million through the Kroger Family of Companies Helping Hands fund to provide financial assistance to associates who face hardship due to COVID-19, including lack of access to childcare and for those considered higher-risk.--sep--Hero Pay Extended Through May 16--sep--Additionally, we are providing all hourly frontline grocery, supply chain, manufacturing, pharmacy and call center associates with a Hero Bonus - a $2 premium above their standard base rate of pay, applied to hours worked March 29 through May 16. The premium will be disbursed weekly to ensure associates have access to additional cash. The Hero Bonus follows and is in addition to our previous commitment shared on March 21, which provided a one time bonus to frontline associates.--sep--Quick Links--sep--Main Page--sep--Learn More--sep--Latest Store Updates--sep--View Past Messages--sep--See How We\u2019re Supporting Communities with Hunger Relief--sep--Last Updated: Sunday, May, 3 2020--sep-- --sep--Connect With Us:--sep--Download the App:--sep--ABOUT THE COMPANY--sep--About the Company--sep--Advertise With Us--sep--Careers--sep--Community--sep--Express HR--sep--Investor Relations--sep--Kroger Real Estate--sep--News Room--sep--Vendors & Suppliers--sep--COMMUNITY--sep--Kroger Community Rewards--sep--Honoring Our Heroes--sep--Sustainability--sep--Request a Donation--sep--CUSTOMER SERVICE--sep--FAQs--sep--Contact Us--sep--Customer Comments--sep--Digital Coupons Policy--sep--My Prescriptions FAQs--sep--Recall Alerts--sep--Feedback--sep--SERVICES--sep--Deli/Bakery Ordering--sep--Digital Coupons--sep--Gift Card Mall--sep--Join Our Customer Panel--sep--Mobile App--sep--Receipt Survey Invitation--sep--Recipes--sep--Shopping List--sep--Store Locator--sep--Weekly Ad--sep--Money Services--sep--GET THE CARD--sep--Learn More--sep--Save on Fuel--sep--Earn Free Groceries--sep--Manage My Card--sep--All Contents \u00a9--sep--2020--sep-- --sep--The Kroger Co.--sep-- --sep--All Rights Reserved--sep--If you are using a screen reader and having difficulty with this website, please call\u00a0--sep--1\u2012800\u2012576\u20124377--sep--.--sep--Pharmacy Privacy Notice--sep--Terms and Conditions--sep--Privacy Policy--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n", "retailer": "kroger"}
