asks.--sep-- --sep-- --sep--Cleaning & Disinfecting Surfaces--sep--All stores are following enhanced cleaning and disinfecting protocols that includes cleaning commonly used areas and wiping down equipment and high touch surfaces more frequently.--sep-- --sep-- --sep--Protective Barriers--sep--We\u2019re installing protective barriers at all check lanes, Pharmacy Counters, Starbucks and The Little Clinic locations, to help protect both customers and associates.--sep-- --sep--Personal Protective Equipment--sep--There is a national shortage of personal protective equipment like this, and we fully support America\u2019s health care workers having first priority to obtain the equipment they need. We are advocating to government officials at all levels for help securing a priority place in line for all grocery workers - after health care workers - to have access to protective masks.--sep--Emergency Leave Guidelines--sep--We have enacted Emergency Leave Guidelines, allowing paid time off for associates diagnosed with COVID-19, placed under mandatory quarantine and paid time off for self isolation and symptoms as verified by an accredited health care professional. All eligible associates will receive their standard pay for up to two weeks (14 days).--sep--For those affected by COVID-19, the organization has also made available $5 million through the Kroger Family of Companies Helping Hands fund to provide financial assistance to associates who face hardship due to COVID-19, including lack of access to childcare and for those considered higher-risk.--sep--Hero Pay Extended Through May 16--sep--Additionally, we are providing all hourly frontline grocery, supply chain, manufacturing, pharmacy and call center associates with a Hero Bonus - a $2 premium above their standard base rate of pay, applied to hours worked March 29 through May 16. The premium will be disbursed weekly to ensure associates have access to additional cash. The Hero Bonus follows and is in addition to our previous commitment shared on March 21, which provided a one time bonus to frontline associates.--sep--Quick Links--sep--Main Page--sep--Learn More--sep--Latest Store Updates--sep--View Past Messages--sep--See How We\u2019re Supporting Communities with Hunger Relief--sep--Last Updated: Sunday, May, 3 2020--sep-- --sep--ABOUT THE COMPANY--sep--About the Company--sep--Advertise With Us--sep--Careers--sep--Community--sep--Express HR--sep--Investor Relations--sep--Kroger Real Estate--sep--News Room--sep--Vendors & Suppliers--sep--COMMUNITY--sep--Kroger Community Rewards--sep--Honoring Our Heroes--sep--Sustainability--sep--Request a Donation--sep--CUSTOMER SERVICE--sep--Help--sep--FAQs--sep--Contact Us--sep--Customer Comments--sep--Digital Coupons Policy--sep--My Prescriptions FAQs--sep--Recall Alerts--sep--Feedback--sep--SERVICES--sep--Deli/Bakery Ordering--sep--Digital Coupons--sep--Gift Cards--sep--Mobile App--sep--Receipt Survey Invitation--sep--Recipes--sep--Shopping List--sep--Store Locator--sep--Weekly Ad--sep--Money Services--sep--GET THE CARD--sep--Learn More--sep--Save on Fuel--sep--Earn Free Groceries--sep--Manage My Card--sep--Get the App--sep--All Contents \u00a92020\n          The Kroger Co.\n            All Rights Reserved--sep--If you are using a screen reader and having difficulty with this website, please call\u00a0--sep--800\u2013576\u20134377--sep--.--sep--Pharmacy Privacy Notice--sep--Terms and Conditions--sep--Privacy Policy--sep--Let's Connect--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n", "retailer": "kroger"}
{"website": "http://web.archive.org/web/20200623094635id_/https://www.kroger.com/i/coronavirus-update/the-little-clinic", "text": "\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--Kroger - The Little Clinic Hours & Services Coronavirus Update--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--Skip to content--sep--Sign In--sep--Popular--sep--Buy 6, Save $.50--sep--Summer Shop--sep--Weekly Ad--sep--Digital Coupons--sep--My Prescriptions--sep--Departments--sep--Summer Shop--sep--At Home--sep--Graduation Shop--sep--Meat and Seafood--sep--Fresh Fruit and Vegetables--sep--Pantry--sep--Natural and Organic--sep--Dairy and Eggs--sep--Floral--sep--Frozen--sep--Deli--sep--Bakery--sep--Beer, Wine and Liquor--sep--Candy--sep--Home and Electronics--sep--Cleaning and Household--sep--Health and Wellness--sep--Beauty--sep--Personal Care--sep--Vitamins and Supplements--sep--Baby--sep--Pet--sep--Ship to Home--sep--Specialty Diets--sep--International Cuisine--sep--Fred Meyer Jewelers--sep--Savings--sep--Our Brands--sep--Discover--sep--Pharmacy and Health--sep--Payments and Services--sep--Search--sep--Clear--sep--Pickup at--sep--\u00a0--sep--Russellville--sep-- --sep--Locations--sep--Sign In--sep--Cart--sep--Hours & Services--sep--At The Little Clinic, we are dedicated to the delivery of high-quality healthcare to our communities, a mission that has not changed. We are currently accepting online and telephone appointments for in-person visits. For your convenience, we now offer virtual care visits as well. We appreciate your patience and understanding as we make adjustments to our hours and services during this time.--sep--Hours:--sep-- For the most up-to-date information on Clinic hours, please visit --sep--The Little Clinic website--sep-- and search for a location near you.--sep--Appointments Only:--sep-- For your safety, and the safety of other patients and associates, we are currently accepting --sep--appointments only--sep-- and are not providing any walk-in services. Please --sep--do not--sep-- come to any Clinic location without an appointment. If you need to visit need to visit The Little Clinic, you can easily --sep--schedule an appointment now--sep--.--sep--In Person Visits - New Process:--sep-- When scheduling an appointment online, all patients will be asked a series of questions regarding specific symptoms.--sep--IMPORTANT: Individuals with symptoms that include --sep--fever, cough and shortness of breath--sep-- should --sep--NOT--sep-- come to a Clinic location. Please visit --sep--The Little Clinic Coronavirus (COVID-19) page--sep-- for more information on what to do if you have any of these symptoms or if you suspect you may have COVID-19. --sep--Virtual Care Visits:--sep-- To support social distancing and to help connect you with healthcare providers, we are working to make virtual care available for our community. Visit The Little Clinic website --sep--to schedule a Virtual Care Visit.--sep--Virtual Dietitian Visits--sep--: Our team of registered dietitian nutritionists is available for virtual consultations to help you develop solutions for weight loss, weight gain, heart health, diabetes, plant-based eating, gluten-free eating or simply well-balanced, nutritional eating. This service is available within the U.S. (with the exceptions of Alaska, Hawaii, Minnesota, Pennsylvania and New York). Visit The Little Clinic website for more information and to schedule --sep--your Virtual Dietitian video chat--sep-- .--sep--Note: The Little Clinic --sep--does not provide testing for COVID-19--sep--. The Kroger Co. is currently partnering with local health departments and other resources to facilitate testing sites for certain individuals meeting CDC criteria for testing. For more information, please visit --sep--www.krogerhealth.com/covidtesting--sep--.--sep--For more information and answers to frequently asked questions on COVID-19 or impacts to The Little Clinic services, please visit --sep--The Little Clinic Coronavirus (COVID-19) page--sep--.--sep--More Helpful Links--sep--Main Page--sep--See Your Store\u2019s Hours--sep--View Policy--sep--See How We We\u2019re Supporting Communities with Hunger Relief--sep--View Hours & Services--sep-- --sep--Connect With Us:--sep--Download the App:--sep--ABOUT THE COMPANY--sep--About the Company--sep--Advertise With Us--sep--Careers--sep--Community--sep--Express HR--sep--Investor Relations--sep--Kroger Real Estate--sep--News Room--sep--Vendors & Suppliers--sep--COMMUNITY--sep--Kroger Community Rewards--sep--Honoring Our Heroes--sep--Sustainability--sep--Request a Donation--sep--CUSTOMER SERVICE--sep--FAQs--sep--Contact Us--sep--Customer Comments--sep--Digital Coupons Policy--sep--My Prescriptions FAQs--sep--Recall Alerts--sep--Feedback--sep--SERVICES--sep--Deli/Bakery Ordering--sep--Digital Coupons--sep--Gift Card Mall--sep--Join Our Customer Panel--sep--Mobile App--sep--Receipt Survey Invitation--sep--Recipes--sep--Shopping List--sep--Store Locator--sep--Weekly Ad--sep--Money Services--sep--GET THE CARD--sep--Learn More--sep--Save on Fuel--sep--Earn Free Groceries--sep--Manage My Card--sep--All Contents \u00a9--sep--2020--sep-- --sep--The Kroger Co.--sep-- --sep--All Rights Reserved--sep--If you are using a screen reader and having difficulty with this website, please call\u00a0--sep--1\u2012800\u2012576\u20124377--sep--.--sep--Pharmacy Privacy Notice--sep--Terms and Conditions--sep--Privacy Policy--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n", "retailer": "kroger"}
{"website": "http://web.archive.org/web/20201020151201id_/https://www.kroger.com/i/coronavirus-update/shopping-guidelines", "text": "\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--Kroger - Safe Grocery Shopping Tips - Coronavirus Update--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--Skip to content--sep--Purchase History--sep--Digital Coupons--sep--Weekly Ad--sep--Shopping List--sep--Find a Store--sep--Payment Cards--sep--Gift Cards--sep--Sign In--sep--Popular--sep--Digital Coupons--sep--Weekly Ad--sep--Buy 5 or More, Save $1 Each--sep--Ship to Home \u2013 NEW! Items--sep--My Prescriptions--sep--Departments--sep--Holiday Gift Guide--sep--Halloween--sep--Candy--sep--Game Day--sep--Fall Flavors--sep--Meat--sep--Fresh Fruit and Vegetables--sep--Pantry--sep--Frozen--sep--Beer, Wine and Liquor--sep--Seafood--sep--Dairy and Eggs--sep--Natural and Organic--sep--Deli--sep--Bakery--sep--Breakfast--sep--Beverages--sep--Home and Electronics--sep--Cleaning and Household--sep--Health and Wellness--sep--Vitamins and Supplements--sep--Personal Care--sep--Beauty--sep--Pet--sep--Floral--sep--Baby--sep--Ship to Home--sep--Specialty Diets--sep--International Cuisine--sep--Fred Meyer Jewelers--sep--Savings--sep--Planning--sep--Our Brands--sep--Discover--sep--Pharmacy and Health--sep--Payments and Services--sep--Search--sep--Clear--sep--Ship to--sep--\u00a0--sep--20146--sep-- --sep--Sign in--sep--Cart--sep--Tips for Safe Grocery Shopping--sep--During this unprecedented time, the health and safety of our customers and associates is our top priority. We\u2019re working hard to keep our stores clean, open and stocked, and to make sure you have a safe experience every time you shop with us. --sep--\u201c[The COVID-19] pandemic is a public health crisis unlike anything we\u2019ve seen in any of our lifetimes,\u201d says Dr. Marc R. Watkins, Chief Medical Officer for Kroger Health. \u201cAnd we\u2019re proud of our associates who are serving on the frontlines to keep our customers and each other safe.\u201d--sep--Dr. Watkins stresses the importance of physical distancing and how we all play a part in reducing the spread of COVID-19. --sep--By taking some simple steps, you can help to protect yourself and others on your next shopping trip. Following recommendations from the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC), and other national and regional authorities, we recommend that you follow these tips for a safe grocery shopping experience:--sep--Wash your hands often. The CDC recommends washing your hands using soap and water, for at least 20 seconds, especially after coughing, blowing your nose or having been in a public place. If you don\u2019t have soap and water, use a sanitizer that contains at least 60% alcohol.--sep--If you don\u2019t feel well, stay home. If you can, order groceries for pickup, delivery or ship to minimize your exposure. You can also have a friend or family member shop for you.--sep--If you do your own shopping, go at a time that\u2019s less busy, like early in the morning or late in the day.--sep--Practice physical distancing. Leave at least 6\u2019 between yourself and other shoppers \u2013 a little more than the length of one shopping cart.--sep--Use sanitizing wipes provided at the store entrance to clean and disinfect your cart or shopping basket.--sep--Avoid touching your face, nose and eyes. --sep--Reduce contact at checkout by using Kroger Pay or a credit or debit card instead of cash.--sep--When you return home, wash your hands after handling packages and putting all your groceries away.--sep--The FDA says there is no evidence of COVID-19 being transmitted on food or its packaging, but it\u2019s always important to properly store and clean fresh produce to prevent other foodborne illnesses. Here are some tips for proper produce handling:--sep--Store fresh fruits and vegetables in a clean refrigerator at 40\u00b0F or below (especially any precut or packaged produce items).--sep--Wash your hands and utensils (knives, cutting boards, etc.) before and between uses, and always keep produce separate from raw meat and seafood.--sep--When preparing fruits and vegetables, cut away any damaged or bruised spots, and discard and produce that looks moldy or rotten. Wash produce under running water and dry with a clean cloth or paper towel before preparing or consuming it.--sep--By practicing these tips, you can do your part to flatten the curve and stay safe. And remember, we\u2019re all in this together! For more information on the steps we\u2019re taking to keep our customers and associates safe, --sep--click here--sep--.--sep-- --sep--ABOUT THE COMPANY--sep--About the Company--sep--Advertise With Us--sep--Careers--sep--Community--sep--Express HR--sep--Investor Relations--sep--Kroger Real Estate--sep--News Room--sep--Vendors & Suppliers--sep--COMMUNITY--sep--Kroger Community Rewards--sep--Honoring Our Heroes--sep--Sustainability--sep--Request a Donation--sep--CUSTOMER SERVICE--sep--Help--sep--FAQs--sep--Contact Us--sep--Customer Comments--sep--Digital Coupons Policy--sep--My Prescriptions FAQs--sep--Recall Alerts--sep--Feedback--sep--SERVICES--sep--Deli/Bakery Ordering--sep--Digital Coupons--sep--Gift Cards--sep--Mobile App--sep--Receipt Survey Invitation--sep--Recipes--sep--Shopping List--sep--Store Locator--sep--Weekly Ad--sep--Money Services--sep--GET THE CARD--sep--Learn More--sep--Save on Fuel--sep--Earn Free Groceries--sep--Manage My Card--sep--Get the App--sep--All Contents \u00a92020\n          The Kroger Co.\n            All Rights Reserved--sep--If you are using a screen reader and having difficulty with this website, please call\u00a0--sep--800\u2013576\u20134377--sep--.--sep--Pharmacy Privacy Notice--sep--Te