{"website": "http://web.archive.org/web/20200821015742id_/https://www.kroger.com/d/flu", "text": "\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--Kroger - Flu Shots - Annual Flu Vaccination--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--Skip to content--sep--Purchase History--sep--Digital Coupons--sep--Weekly Ad--sep--Shopping List--sep--Find a Store--sep--Payment Cards--sep--Gift Cards--sep--Sign In--sep--Popular--sep--Digital Coupons--sep--Weekly Ad--sep--Buy 5 or More, Save $1 Each--sep--Face Masks, Sanitizers & More--sep--My Prescriptions--sep--Departments--sep--School Essentials--sep--Summer Shop--sep--Adventure Kids Camp--sep--Meat--sep--Fresh Fruit and Vegetables--sep--Pantry--sep--Frozen--sep--Beer, Wine and Liquor--sep--Seafood--sep--Dairy and Eggs--sep--Natural and Organic--sep--Deli--sep--Bakery--sep--Breakfast--sep--Beverages--sep--Home and Electronics--sep--Cleaning and Household--sep--Health and Wellness--sep--Vitamins and Supplements--sep--Personal Care--sep--Beauty--sep--Pet--sep--Candy--sep--Floral--sep--Baby--sep--Ship to Home--sep--Specialty Diets--sep--International Cuisine--sep--Fred Meyer Jewelers--sep--Savings--sep--Planning--sep--Our Brands--sep--Discover--sep--Pharmacy and Health--sep--Payments and Services--sep--Search--sep--Clear--sep--Ship to--sep--\u00a0--sep--94102--sep-- --sep--Sign in--sep--Cart--sep--Did you know getting the right vaccinations can help minimize the chances of getting sick? If you do get the flu, being vacci nated may help reduce the severity of symptoms and risk for complications.--sep--Your health and safety is our priority, and we encourage you to use these helpful online tools prior to your visit. To make a vaccine appointment at The Little Clinic, please --sep--click here.--sep--Tools to Make Your Vaccine Appointment Even Easier--sep-- --sep--\u00a0--sep-- --sep-- --sep-- --sep-- --sep--\u00a0--sep-- --sep--The following Frequently Asked Questions were created following guidance from the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC).--sep--What is the flu?--sep--Influenza, better known simply as the flu, is a contagious respiratory illness caused by viruses that infect the nose, throat and sometimes the lungs. It can cause mild to severe illness and, at times, can even lead to death. The best way to prevent the flu is by getting a flu vaccine each year.--sep--Why is getting a flu vaccine important?--sep--Older people, young children and people with certain health conditions are at higher risk for serious flu complications. If you do get the flu, being vaccinated may help reduce the severity of symptoms and risk for complications. This flu season, it is more important than ever to get a flu vaccine. The flu vaccine will not protect against COVID-19, but it will reduce the risk of flu illness, hospitalization and death, thereby helping conserve potentially scarce healthcare resources.--sep--Who should get the flu vaccine?--sep--People age 6 months and older are eligible to receive an annual seasonal flu vaccine, with rare exceptions that include those with allergies. Talk to your licensed healthcare provider to learn which type of flu vaccine is right for you.--sep--How often should I get the flu vaccine?--sep--Getting the seasonal flu vaccine annually (once a year) is the best way to reduce your risk of catching the seasonal flu and spreading it to others. September and October are ideal months to get your flu shot.--sep--What types of flu vaccines are available?--sep--The CDC recommends injectable influenza vaccines. There is no preference for one flu vaccine over another as long as the vaccine is licensed and age appropriate.--sep--Can I get the flu from a flu shot?--sep--No. The flu shot contains inactivated virus, so you cannot get the flu from the vaccine.--sep--Explore other Vaccines--sep-- --sep--\u00a0--sep-- --sep-- --sep--\u00a0--sep-- --sep-- --sep--\u00a0--sep-- --sep--Keep on Exploring Health and Wellness--sep-- --sep--ABOUT THE COMPANY--sep--About the Company--sep--Advertise With Us--sep--Careers--sep--Community--sep--Express HR--sep--Investor Relations--sep--Kroger Real Estate--sep--News Room--sep--Vendors & Suppliers--sep--COMMUNITY--sep--Kroger Community Rewards--sep--Honoring Our Heroes--sep--Sustainability--sep--Request a Donation--sep--CUSTOMER SERVICE--sep--Help--sep--FAQs--sep--Contact Us--sep--Customer Comments--sep--Digital Coupons Policy--sep--My Prescriptions FAQs--sep--Recall Alerts--sep--Feedback--sep--SERVICES--sep--Deli/Bakery Ordering--sep--Digital Coupons--sep--Gift Card Mall--sep--Mobile App--sep--Receipt Survey Invitation--sep--Recipes--sep--Shopping List--sep--Store Locator--sep--Weekly Ad--sep--Money Services--sep--GET THE CARD--sep--Learn More--sep--Save on Fuel--sep--Earn Free Groceries--sep--Manage My Card--sep--Get the App--sep--All Contents \u00a92020\n          The Kroger Co.\n            All Rights Reserved--sep--If you are using a screen reader and having difficulty with this website, please call\u00a0--sep--1\u2012800\u2012576\u20124377--sep--.--sep--Pharmacy Privacy Notice--sep--Terms and Conditions--sep--Privacy Policy--sep--Let's Connect--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n", "retailer": "kroger"}
