{"website": "http://web.archive.org/web/20200318022435id_/https://www.kroger.com/i/coronavirus-update", "text": "\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--Kroger - Coronavirus Update--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--Skip to content--sep--Kroger--sep--Ship--sep--Sign In--sep--Popular--sep--Digital Coupons--sep--My Prescriptions--sep--The Little Clinic--sep--Purchase History--sep--Departments--sep--Quick and Easy Meal Solutions--sep--Family Night In--sep--Easter Shop--sep--Fish and Meatless Shop--sep--Pantry--sep--Meat and Seafood--sep--Fresh Fruit and Vegetables--sep--Natural and Organic--sep--Dairy and Eggs--sep--Frozen--sep--Deli--sep--Bakery--sep--Beer, Wine and Liquor--sep--Candy--sep--Home and Electronics--sep--Cleaning and Household Essentials--sep--Health and Wellness--sep--Beauty--sep--Personal Care--sep--Vitamins and Supplements--sep--Baby--sep--Pet--sep--Specialty Diets--sep--International Cuisine--sep--Fred Meyer Jewelers--sep--Savings--sep--Shop by Brand--sep--Discover--sep--Pharmacy and Health--sep--Search Products--sep--Search Icon--sep--Pickup at--sep--\u00a0--sep--Russellville--sep--Locations--sep--Sign In--sep--Cart--sep--Gift Cards--sep--Lists--sep--Weekly Ad--sep--Digital Coupons--sep--Our Payment Cards--sep--Help--sep--A Message from The Kroger Co. CEO Rodney McMullen About the Coronavirus \u2014 --sep--We're Here for Our Customers & Communities--sep--At Kroger, our customers are like family. And like you, during these last few weeks we\u2019ve been focused on doing all the things we need to do to keep our families safe and healthy.--sep--As America\u2019s grocer, we\u2019re here for our customers and communities when they need us most, with open stores and openhearted hospitality. --sep--We believe that everyone deserves to have access to fresh, affordable food and essentials, especially in times of uncertainty. That\u2019s why our teams are working so hard to keep our stores clean, open and stocked. That\u2019s why we took the precautionary step on March 2 to limit the number of cold, flu and sanitary products per order\u2026so everyone can have access to the items they need. And that\u2019s why our supply chain teams are working to ensure that the food, medicine and cleaning supplies our customers need are reaching our stores as quickly as possible and are available through our pickup, delivery and ship services. --sep--We activated our preparedness plan several weeks ago, and we continue to monitor the rapidly evolving situation. We\u2019re following guidance from federal, state and local agencies, including the CDC and other health organizations. --sep--Here are the steps we\u2019re taking to protect our customers and associates: --sep--In Our Stores--sep--Cleaning commonly used areas more often, including cashier stations, self-checkouts, credit card terminals, conveyor belts and food service counters, and cleaning shelves when restocking products.--sep--Sanitizing restrooms more frequently and restocking with supplies, including soap, paper towels and hand sanitizer.--sep--Adding extra hand sanitizer at cashier stations, food service counters, and all Pharmacy, The Little Clinic and Starbucks locations.--sep--Wiping down shopping carts, baskets and equipment. --sep--Partnering with our suppliers to replenish high-demand preparedness products.--sep--Continuing to provide our customers with free disinfectant wipes at our store entrances to sanitize their shopping carts or baskets.--sep--Following best practices for safe food handling, as always. --sep--For Our Associates --sep--Encouraging our associates to closely monitor their health and well-being.--sep--Providing hand sanitizer and tissues in breakrooms and meeting rooms.--sep--Asking our associates to stay home if they, or someone in their household, are sick. --sep--Providing financial support from our Helping Hands fund \u2013 a company-sponsored employee assistance fund \u2013 to associates who may be directly affected.--sep--Suspending business air travel for associates through March 31, 2020 and recommending virtual meetings. --sep--For Our Customers --sep--Encouraging our customers to follow the --sep--CDC\u2019s suggested hygiene practices--sep-- to reduce the spread of the virus.--sep--Recommending that our customers also practice safe food handling at home. --sep--In everything we do, we\u2019re guided by our values and our Purpose: to Feed the Human Spirit. We strive to make decisions that balance the safety of our associates with our commitments to our customers and communities. And above all else, we\u2019ll be there for our communities when they need us most. --sep--Thank you for being a loyal customer,--sep--Rodney McMullen--sep--Chairman and CEO--sep-- --sep--Connect With Us:--sep--Download the App:--sep--ABOUT THE COMPANY--sep--About the Company--sep--Advertise With Us--sep--Careers--sep--Community--sep--Express HR--sep--Investor Relations--sep--Kroger Real Estate--sep--News Room--sep--Vendors & Suppliers--sep--COMMUNITY--sep--Kroger Community Rewards--sep--Honoring Our Heroes--sep--Sustainability--sep--Request a Donation--sep--CUSTOMER SERVICE--sep--FAQs--sep--Contact Us--sep--Customer Comments--sep--Digital Coupons Policy--sep--My Prescriptions FAQs--sep--Recall Alerts--sep--Feedback--sep--SERVICES--sep--Deli/Bakery Ordering--sep--Digital Coupons--sep--Gift Card Mall--sep--Join Our Customer Panel--sep--Mobile App--sep--Receipt Survey Invitation--sep--Recipes--sep--Shopping List--sep--Store Locator--sep--Weekly Ad--sep--Money Services--sep--GET THE CARD--sep--Learn More--sep--Save on Fuel--sep--Earn Free Groceries--sep--Manage My Card--sep--All Contents \u00a9--sep--2020--sep-- --sep--The 