--Download the App--sep--Store Information & Safety Measures--sep--We\u2019re taking serious measures to protect both our customers and associates.--sep--Customer Capacity Limits--sep--Beginning April 7, The Kroger Co. will begin to limit the number of customers to 50% of the international building code\u2019s calculated capacity to allow for proper physical distancing in every store. --sep--Read the full press release here--sep-- and --sep--read related FAQs here--sep--.--sep--Easter Sunday Hours--sep--The Kroger Family of Companies is closing early on Easter Sunday, April 12, to provide its associates with more time to rest and be with their families. Holiday operating hours will vary by location and market. --sep--See hours here--sep--. --sep--Cleaning and Disinfecting--sep--All stores are following enhanced cleaning and disinfecting protocols that includes cleaning commonly used areas and wiping down equipment and high-touch surfaces.--sep--Protective Barriers--sep--We\u2019re installing protective barriers at check lanes and Pharmacy counters (as well as The Little Clinic and Starbucks) to protect both customers and associates.--sep--Social Distancing--sep--As part of our efforts to keep you safe and to encourage social distancing, you may notice signage or floor markers at some locations that encourage proper physical distance between yourself and other shoppers.--sep--Exclusive Shopping Hours for Seniors--sep--Certain stores have --sep--Exclusive Shopping Hours--sep-- for seniors 60 and over; however, Pharmacy and clinic hours for each store may vary.--sep--Associate Wellbeing & Safety--sep--Our associates are on the frontlines, ensuring Americans have access to the food, services and products they need during this unprecedented pandemic. We are committed to protecting the health and safety of our associates.--sep--Protective Face Masks and Gloves for Associates--sep--We\u2019ve let our associates know they are permitted to wear protective masks and gloves, and we are working hard to secure these resources. There is a national shortage of personal protective equipment like this, and we fully support America\u2019s health care workers having first priority to obtain the equipment they need. We are advocating to government officials at all levels for help securing a priority place in line for all grocery workers - after health care workers - to have access to protective masks and gloves.--sep--Emergency Leave Guidelines--sep--We have enacted Emergency Leave Guidelines, allowing paid time off for associates diagnosed with COVID-19, placed under mandatory quarantine and paid time off for self-isolation and symptoms as verified by an accredited health care professional. All eligible associates will receive their standard pay for up to two weeks (14 days).--sep--For those affected by COVID-19, the organization has also made available $5 million through the Kroger Family of Companies Helping Hands fund to provide financial assistance to associates who face hardship due to COVID-19, including lack of access to childcare and for those considered higher-risk.--sep--Hero Pay--sep--Additionally, we are providing all hourly frontline grocery, supply chain, manufacturing, pharmacy and call center associates with a Hero Bonus \u2013 a $2 premium above their standard base rate of pay, applied to hours worked March 29 through April 18. The premium will be disbursed weekly to ensure associates have access to additional cash. The Hero Bonus follows and is in addition to our previous commitment shared on March 21, which provided a one-time bonus to frontline associates.--sep--Community--sep--The Kroger Co. Zero Hunger | Zero Waste Foundation has committed more than $5 million to support our neighbors during the COVID-19 pandemic. These grants are funding local food banks and ensuring children with school closures have access to nutritious meals. Join us in our Zero Hunger | Zero Waste mission by donating today to our Emergency COVID-19 Response Fund either --sep--online--sep-- or by rounding up your purchase to the nearest dollar or committing $1, $5 or $10.--sep--Free Pickup--sep--Due to increased demand, you may experience longer wait times, limited inventory, limited pickup time slots or delayed deliveries. Our associates are working around the clock to make it easier for you to get what you need. In the meantime, we invite you to try our FREE pickup service at a store near you.--sep--More Helpful Links--sep--Kroger Pay--sep--Ways to Shop--sep--Learn More--sep--Safe Grocery Shopping Tips--sep--View Past Messages--sep-- --sep--Connect With Us:--sep--Download the App:--sep--ABOUT THE COMPANY--sep--About the Company--sep--Advertise With Us--sep--Careers--sep--Community--sep--Express HR--sep--Investor Relations--sep--Kroger Real Estate--sep--News Room--sep--Vendors & Suppliers--sep--COMMUNITY--sep--Kroger Community Rewards--sep--Honoring Our Heroes--sep--Sustainability--sep--Request a Donation--sep--CUSTOMER SERVICE--sep--FAQs--sep--Contact Us--sep--Customer Comments--sep--Digital Coupons Policy--sep--My Prescriptions FAQs--sep--Recall Alerts--sep--Feedback--sep--SERVICES--sep--Deli/Bakery Ordering--sep--Digital Coupons--sep--Gift Card Mall--sep--Join Our Customer Panel--sep--Mobile App--sep--Receipt Survey Invitation--sep--Recipes--sep--Shopping List--sep--Store Locator--sep--Weekly Ad--sep--Money Services--sep--GET THE CARD--sep--Learn More--sep--Save on Fuel--sep--Earn Free Groceries--sep--Manage My Card--sep--All Contents \u00a9--sep--2020--sep-- --sep--The Kroger Co.--sep-- --sep--All Rights Reserved--sep--If you are using a screen reader and having difficulty with this website, please call\u00a0--sep--1\u2012800\u2012576\u20124377--sep--.--sep--Pharmacy Privacy Notice--sep--Terms and Conditions--sep--Privacy Policy--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n", "retailer": "kroger"}
