equipment they need. We are advocating to government officials at all levels for help securing a priority place in line for all grocery workers - after health care workers - to have access to protective masks and gloves.--sep--Emergency Leave Guidelines--sep--We have enacted Emergency Leave Guidelines, allowing paid time off for associates diagnosed with COVID-19, placed under mandatory quarantine and paid time off for self-isolation and symptoms as verified by an accredited health care professional. All eligible associates will receive their standard pay for up to two weeks (14 days).--sep--For those affected by COVID-19, the organization has also made available $5 million through the Kroger Family of Companies Helping Hands fund to provide financial assistance to associates who face hardship due to COVID-19, including lack of access to childcare and for those considered higher-risk.--sep--Hero Pay--sep--Additionally, we are providing all hourly frontline grocery, supply chain, manufacturing, pharmacy and call center associates with a Hero Bonus \u2013 a $2 premium above their standard base rate of pay, applied to hours worked March 29 through April 18. The premium will be disbursed weekly to ensure associates have access to additional cash. The Hero Bonus follows and is in addition to our previous commitment shared on March 21, which provided a one-time bonus to frontline associates.--sep--Community--sep--The Kroger Co. Zero Hunger | Zero Waste Foundation has committed more than $5 million to support our neighbors during the COVID-19 pandemic. These grants are funding local food banks and ensuring children with school closures have access to nutritious meals. Join us in our Zero Hunger | Zero Waste mission by donating today to our Emergency COVID-19 Response Fund either --sep--online--sep-- or by rounding up your purchase to the nearest dollar or committing $1, $5 or $10.--sep--Free Pickup--sep--Due to increased demand, you may experience longer wait times, limited inventory, limited pickup time slots or delayed deliveries. Our associates are working around the clock to make it easier for you to get what you need. In the meantime, we invite you to try our FREE pickup service at a store near you.--sep--More Helpful Links--sep--Main Page--sep--See Your Store\u2019s Hours--sep--View Policy--sep--Apply Today--sep--See How We We\u2019re Supporting Communities with Hunger Relief--sep--See Clinic Updates--sep-- --sep--Connect With Us:--sep--Download the App:--sep--ABOUT THE COMPANY--sep--About the Company--sep--Advertise With Us--sep--Careers--sep--Community--sep--Express HR--sep--Investor Relations--sep--Kroger Real Estate--sep--News Room--sep--Vendors & Suppliers--sep--COMMUNITY--sep--Kroger Community Rewards--sep--Honoring Our Heroes--sep--Sustainability--sep--Request a Donation--sep--CUSTOMER SERVICE--sep--FAQs--sep--Contact Us--sep--Customer Comments--sep--Digital Coupons Policy--sep--My Prescriptions FAQs--sep--Recall Alerts--sep--Feedback--sep--SERVICES--sep--Deli/Bakery Ordering--sep--Digital Coupons--sep--Gift Card Mall--sep--Join Our Customer Panel--sep--Mobile App--sep--Receipt Survey Invitation--sep--Recipes--sep--Shopping List--sep--Store Locator--sep--Weekly Ad--sep--Money Services--sep--GET THE CARD--sep--Learn More--sep--Save on Fuel--sep--Earn Free Groceries--sep--Manage My Card--sep--All Contents \u00a9--sep--2020--sep-- --sep--The Kroger Co.--sep-- --sep--All Rights Reserved--sep--If you are using a screen reader and having difficulty with this website, please call\u00a0--sep--1\u2012800\u2012576\u20124377--sep--.--sep--Pharmacy Privacy Notice--sep--Terms and Conditions--sep--Privacy Policy--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n", "retailer": "kroger"}
