{"website": "http://web.archive.org/web/20200807015700id_/https://www.kroger.com/i/kroger-research-panel", "text": "\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--Kroger - Research Panel--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--Skip to content--sep--Purchase History--sep--Digital Coupons--sep--Weekly Ad--sep--Shopping List--sep--Find a Store--sep--Payment Cards--sep--Gift Cards--sep--Sign In--sep--Popular--sep--Digital Coupons--sep--Weekly Ad--sep--Buy 5 or More, Save $1 Each--sep--Ways to Shop--sep--My Prescriptions--sep--Departments--sep--Summer Shop--sep--School Essentials--sep--Adventure Kids Camp--sep--Meat--sep--Fresh Fruit and Vegetables--sep--Pantry--sep--Frozen--sep--Beer, Wine and Liquor--sep--Seafood--sep--Dairy and Eggs--sep--Natural and Organic--sep--Deli--sep--Bakery--sep--Home and Electronics--sep--Cleaning and Household--sep--Health and Wellness--sep--Vitamins and Supplements--sep--Personal Care--sep--Beauty--sep--Pet--sep--Candy--sep--Floral--sep--Baby--sep--Ship to Home--sep--Specialty Diets--sep--International Cuisine--sep--Fred Meyer Jewelers--sep--Savings--sep--Planning--sep--Our Brands--sep--Discover--sep--Pharmacy and Health--sep--Payments and Services--sep--Search--sep--Clear--sep--Ship to--sep--\u00a0--sep--20146--sep-- --sep--Locations--sep--Sign in--sep--Cart--sep--Kroger wants your feedback on how to make grocery shopping as simple and enjoyable as possible! By joining our panel, and participating in periodic user research studies, you can help us improve both our online and in-store experiences, while earning a little something as a token of our appreciation.--sep-- --sep--Enter Your Info--sep--Enter some basic information so we can enroll you in our user research panel, and the studies that best match your shopping habits. Sign up should take less than 10 minutes.--sep-- --sep-- --sep--Enter Your Info--sep--Enter some basic information so we can enroll you in our user research panel, and the studies that best match your shopping habits. Sign up should take less than 10 minutes.--sep-- --sep-- --sep-- --sep--Participate--sep--Once we have your info, we\u2019ll see if we can find a study that\u2019s a good match for you. If we do, we\u2019ll reach out via email or phone call. At this time, we\u2019ll also fill you in on the study specifics and how you\u2019ll be compensated. Many of our studies can be done from your home through your computer or mobile device. Remember, even if we match you with a study you can always decline to participate if you\u2019re not interested.--sep-- --sep-- --sep--Participate--sep--Once we have your info, we\u2019ll see if we can find a study that\u2019s a good match for you. If we do, we\u2019ll reach out via email or phone call. At this time, we\u2019ll also fill you in on the study specifics and how you\u2019ll be compensated. Many of our studies can be done from your home through your computer or mobile device. Remember, even if we match you with a study you can always decline to participate if you\u2019re not interested.--sep-- --sep--Get Rewarded--sep--You ate all your dinner, now it's time for dessert! After completing your study, we'll send your compensation right away. Examples include gift cards, discounts or free products.--sep-- --sep-- --sep--Get Rewarded--sep--You ate all your dinner, now it's time for dessert! After completing your study, we'll send your compensation right away. Examples include gift cards, discounts or free products.--sep-- --sep--Thanks for the Help!--sep--We look forward to meeting you, regardless of whether or not you're a current customer. Your input helps us improve the grocery experience for everyone.--sep--FAQ's--sep--How are you following COVID-19 safety best practices?--sep--Safety is our first priority, and we will follow best practices to protect everyone\u2019s health. Until it is safe to do so, we will be holding our research studies with customers remotely, primarily through video conferencing tools.--sep--Do I need to be a Kroger/Kroger-affiliated customer?--sep--No. We love to hear feedback from both current customers and people who have never shopped with us.--sep--How quickly will I be compensated?--sep--You will be compensated immediately after you finish the study. For longer-term studies this may vary.--sep--What if I don't live near a Kroger or Kroger-affiliate?--sep--Not a problem! Many of our studies can be conducted remotely via phone or video calls.--sep--If I have a disability of any sort can I still participate?--sep--Yes! Your feedback is exceptionally valuable, as we aim to make our online and in-store experiences accessible for everyone. If you have questions about how we accommodate for disabilities, please email UserResearch@kroger.com.--sep--Will I get spam emails if I sign up?--sep--No. We will only send you emails regarding study participation, and your information will be protected and kept private.--sep--What if I need to update my contact information?--sep--Please send an email to UserResearch@kroger.com with the specific information that needs to be updated.--sep--Can I opt out anytime, and how?--sep--You can do so at any time. To opt out please send an email to UserResearch@kroger.com specifying that you no longer wish to participate in our studies.--sep--When should I expect to be contacted to do a study?--sep--You'll receive a confirmation email after signing up, but from this point on we'll only contact you if you're a fit for an upcoming study.--sep--If I say no to the first study, will I be contacted again?--sep--Declining one study does not exclude you from future participation. The only way we'll count you out is if you tell us you'd no longer like to participate in future studies.--sep--How long should I expect a study to take?--sep--Typically, studies last about 30-60 minutes, depending upon the type. There are exceptions for long-term studies, but you'll know the approximate length before you accept an invitation to join a study.--sep--What types of people are you looking for?--sep--Anyone who grocery shops! Which is...everyone! We're always looking for a diverse set of participants. If you have any questions at all, please feel free to contact us at UserResearch@kroger.com.--sep--What will I be doing if I participate?--sep--Studies can come in many forms. Examples include:--sep--Remote and in-person interviews, surveys, thought exercises, testing prototypes, and long-term studies.--sep-- --sep--About The Company--sep--About the Company--sep--Advertise With Us--sep--Careers--sep--Community--sep--Express HR--sep--Investor Relations--sep--Kroger Real Estate--sep--News Room--sep--Vendors & Suppliers--sep--Community--sep--Kroger Community Rewards--sep--Honoring Our Heroes--sep--Sustainability--sep--Request a Donation--sep--Customer Service--sep--Help--sep--FAQs--sep--Contact Us--sep--Customer Comments--sep--Digital Coupons Policy--sep--My Prescriptions FAQs--sep--Recall Alerts--sep--Feedback--sep--Services--sep--Deli/Bakery Ordering--sep--Digital Coupons--sep--Gift Card Mall--sep--Join Our Customer Panel--sep--Mobile App--sep--Receipt Survey Invitation--sep--Recipes--sep--Shopping List--sep--Store Locator--sep--Weekly Ad--sep--Money Services--sep--Get The Card--sep--Learn More--sep--Save on Fuel--sep--Earn Free Groceries--sep--Manage My Card--sep--Get the App--sep--All Contents \u00a9--sep--2020\n          The Kroger Co.\n            All Rights Reserved--sep--If you are using a screen reader and having difficulty with this website, please call\u00a0--sep--1\u2012800\u2012576\u20124377--sep--.--sep--Pharmacy Privacy Notice--sep--Terms and Conditions--sep--Privacy Policy--sep--Let's Connect--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n", "retailer": "kroger"}
