ons. Plus, save time by paying online and getting notified when your prescriptions are ready. --sep--Find out how to sign up for My Prescriptions now--sep--.--sep--Free Prescription Delivery--sep--Through June 30, we have temporarily waived fees for prescription delivery via mail or courier. In many areas, if your order is placed by 11 a.m. local time, it can be processed the same day; orders placed after 11 a.m. local time will be processed the following business day. To learn more about options and availability, please contact your local Pharmacy directly.--sep--Kroger Rx Savings Club, powered by GoodRx*--sep--Kroger Rx Savings Club is an easy, low-cost solution to high deductibles and copays, expensive medications and prescriptions not covered by a benefit plan. Individual membership is just $36 per year, and family membership (up to six people, including pet s) is only $72 annually.--sep--Members can save up to 85% on thousands of prescriptions - both generic and name brand. Hundreds of prescriptions are $3, $6 and even FREE. Visit --sep--Krogersc.com--sep--.--sep--*Not valid in Washington state--sep--The Little Clinic*--sep--To protect the safety of our patients, associates and shoppers, The Little Clinic is now offering virtual care visits in select states, in addition to in-clinic appointments. Visit --sep--The Little Clinic website--sep-- to set up your appointment or view your local Clinic Clinic\u2019s operating hours.--sep--*Available in select locations--sep--A Message From Kroger Health--sep--Safety Measures--sep--We\u2019re taking serious measures to protect both our Pharmacy customers and associates.--sep--Cleaning and Disinfecting: --sep--All stores are following enhanced cleaning and disinfecting protocols that includes cleaning commonly used areas and wiping down equipment and high-touch surfaces.--sep--Protective Barriers:--sep-- We\u2019re installing protective barriers at check lanes and Pharmacy counters (as well as The Little Clinic and Starbucks) to protect both customers and associates.--sep--Social Distancing:--sep-- As part of our efforts to keep you safe and to encourage social distancing, you may notice signage or floor markers at Pharmacy counters and Clinics that encourage proper physical distance between yourself and other shoppers.--sep--Exclusive Shopping Hours for Seniors:--sep-- Certain stores have --sep--Exclusive Shopping Hours--sep-- for seniors 60 & over; however, Pharmacy & clinic hours for each store may vary.--sep--Store Capacity Limits:--sep-- In addition to established physical distancing precautions, beginning April 7, our stores will proactively adopt Capacity Limits to further encourage safe physical distancing in stores.--sep--Frequently Asked Questions (FAQs)--sep--Is COVID-19 testing available at your Pharmacies?--sep--Testing is not available at Pharmacy locations. The Kroger Co. is currently partnering with local health departments and other resources to facilitate testing sites for certain individuals meeting CDC criteria for testing. For more information, please visit --sep--www.krogerhealth.com/covidtesting--sep--What are the symptoms of COVID-19?--sep--For the latest information on COVID-19 symptoms and what you can do to better protect yourself, please refer to the --sep--Centers for Disease Control and Prevention--sep--.--sep--How are you supporting seniors during this time?--sep--Certain stores have --sep--Exclusive Shopping Hours--sep-- for seniors 60 & over; however, Pharmacy hours for each store may vary.--sep--Are Pharmacists still giving vaccines?--sep--Yes. We offer a complete line of vaccinations, including flu, shingles, hepatitis, meningitis and more, with no appointment necessary. To protect our associates, other customers, and you, we will provide you a mask to wear while receiving your vaccine if you don don\u2019t have one. Visit --sep--our Vaccinations page--sep-- for more information.--sep--Are you offering additional product for purchase at Pharmacy drive thru?--sep--Certain over the counter products used for cold, cough, and flu may be available for purchase through the drive thru, while supplies last.--sep--How can I save money on my prescriptions?--sep--With Kroger Rx Savings Club, you can save up to 85% on thousands of prescriptions - both generic and name brand. Visit --sep--Krogersc.com--sep-- or download the KrogerRxSC App for more information or to join the club. (Note: This service is currently not valid in Washington state.)--sep--How do I get early refills on maintenance medications?--sep--Your health plan may provide exemptions or overrides during this time; however, all state and federal laws still apply. Check with your plan to see if they will allow early refills on maintenance medications (prescriptions you need to take regularly).--sep--How do I get enough medication so I can practice social distancing as long as possible?--sep--You can make fewer trips to the Pharmacy by enrolling in Sync Up or switching to a 90-day supply for many prescription medications.* Sync Up allows you to pick up all of your medications in one visit. With these services, it it\u2019s easier to adhere to maintenance medication plans, improving health outcomes. Talk to your Pharmacist today to learn more. (*Restrictions and exclusions apply. See Pharmacy for details.)--sep--How do I get medication if I can can\u2019t leave my house?--sep--You can have your medication delivered. Through June 30, we are temporarily waiving fees for prescription delivery via mail or courier. In many areas, if your order is placed by 11 a.m. local time, it can be processed the same day; orders placed after 11 a.m. local time will be processed the following business day. To learn more about the options and availability at your local pharmacy location, please contact your Pharmacy directly.--sep--More Helpful Links--sep--Main Page--sep--See Your Store\u2019s Hours--sep--View Policy--sep--See How We We\u2019re Supporting Communities with Hunger Relief--sep--See Clinic Updates--sep-- --sep--Connect With Us:--sep--Download the App:--sep--ABOUT THE COMPANY--sep--About the Company--sep--Advertise With Us--sep--Careers--sep--Community--sep--Express HR--sep--Investor Relations--sep--Kroger Real Estate--sep--News Room--sep--Vendors & Suppliers--sep--COMMUNITY--sep--Kroger Community Rewards--sep--Honoring Our Heroes--sep--Sustainability--sep--Request a Donation--sep--CUSTOMER SERVICE--sep--FAQs--sep--Contact Us--sep--Customer Comments--sep--Digital Coupons Policy--sep--My Prescriptions FAQs--sep--Recall Alerts--sep--Feedback--sep--SERVICES--sep--Deli/Bakery Ordering--sep--Digital Coupons--sep--Gift Card Mall--sep--Join Our Customer Panel--sep--Mobile App--sep--Receipt Survey Invitation--sep--Recipes--sep--Shopping List--sep--Store Locator--sep--Weekly Ad--sep--Money Services--sep--GET THE CARD--sep--Learn More--sep--Save on Fuel--sep--Earn Free Groceries--sep--Manage My Card--sep--All Contents \u00a9--sep--2020--sep-- --sep--The Kroger Co.--sep-- --sep--All Rights Reserved--sep--If you are using a screen reader and having difficulty with this website, please call\u00a0--sep--1\u2012800\u2012576\u20124377--sep--.--sep--Pharmacy Privacy Notice--sep--Terms and Conditions--sep--Privacy Policy--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n--sep--\n", "retailer": "kroger"}
